## Context
React 19 eliminates the need for `forwardRef` when passing ref to components. We can now directly use `ref` as a prop:

```tsx
const MyButton = ({ ref, ...props }: ComponentProps<"button">) => {
  return <button ref={ref} {...props} />;
};
```

## Goal

Refactor components that currently use `forwardRef` to use React 19's native `ref` prop.


## Example

BEFORE :

```tsx
type SomeCustomProps = {
  color: "red" | "blue";
} & ComponentPropsWithoutRef<"div">;

export const MyCustomComponent = forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, SomeCustomProps>(
  ({ color, ...props }, ref) => {
    return <div ref={ref} {...props} />;
  },
);
```

AFTER :

```tsx
type SomeCustomProps = {
  color: "red" | "blue";
} & ComponentProps<"div">;

export const MyCustomComponent = ({
  color,
  ref,
  ...props
}: SomeCustomProps) => {
  return <div ref={ref} {...props} />;
};
```
